<subSubSection id="91CD80F6D726525E9090A096FC946B93" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D968D37DD726525E9090A096FC946B93" blockId="8.[490,1556,1181,1482]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">
The 
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E936DA096FD4B6AEC" box="[534,660,1181,1205]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Persea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mite">Persea mite</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E93DFA096FCC86AEC" authorityName="Tuttle, Baker &amp; Abbatiello" authorityYear="1976" box="[676,791,1181,1205]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetranychidae" genus="Oligonychus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perseae">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E93DFA096FCC86AEC" box="[676,791,1181,1205]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">O. perseae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, was detected on 
<collectingRegion id="1B131D9FD726525E9296A096FB8E6AEC" box="[1005,1105,1181,1205]" country="Portugal" name="Madeira" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Madeira</collectingRegion>
Island in 2005 associated with avocado (
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E9088A0CBFD686A8E" box="[499,695,1216,1239]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Lauraceae" genus="Persea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Laurales" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="americana">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E9088A0CBFD686A8E" box="[499,695,1216,1239]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Persea americana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), grapes (
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E9258A0CBFC4E6A8E" box="[803,913,1215,1239]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Vitaceae" genus="Vitis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Vitales" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vinifera">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E9258A0CBFC4E6A8E" box="[803,913,1215,1239]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">V. vinifera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), European plum (
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E9527A0CBFB3C6A8E" box="[1116,1251,1215,1239]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="domestica">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E9527A0CBFB3C6A8E" box="[1116,1251,1215,1239]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">P. domestica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the ornamentals 
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E9091A0E8FD7E6AA3" box="[490,673,1251,1274]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Wisteria" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sinensis">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E9091A0E8FD7E6AA3" box="[490,673,1251,1274]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Wisteria sinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E93AFA0E9FB526AA3" authority="(Ferreira et al. 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Ferreira" baseAuthorityYear="2006" box="[724,1165,1250,1274]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Bauhinia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="variegata">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E93AFA0E9FC746AA3" box="[724,939,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Bauhinia variegata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="BD46AE8CD726525E92CAA0E9FB596AA3" author="Ferreira M. A. S. &amp; Brazao C. I. &amp; Aguiar A. F." box="[945,1158,1250,1274]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" pagination="219 - 222" refId="ref9545" refString="Ferreira M. A. S., Brazao C. I., Aguiar A. F. 2006. Ocorrencia de Oligonychus perseae Tuttle, Baker &amp; Abbatiello (Acari: Tetranychidae) na Ilha da Madeira. Agronomia Lusitana, 51: 219 - 222." type="journal article" year="2006">
Ferreira 
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E9574A0E8FB976AA3" box="[1039,1096,1250,1274]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">et al.</emphasis>
2006
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. In 2006, it was found in the Algarve (mainland 
<collectingCountry id="A1C093EDD726525E93B8A10FFCFB6B45" box="[707,804,1284,1308]" name="Portugal" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Portugal</collectingCountry>
), associated mainly with avocado (Hass, Reed and Bacon cultivars), but also with carob trees (
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E9277A12CFC166B66" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[780,969,1319,1343]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Ceratonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="siliqua">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E9277A12CFC166B66" box="[780,969,1319,1343]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Ceratonia siliqua</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Sweet cherry (
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E95FFA123FAC46B66" box="[1156,1307,1320,1343]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="avium">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E95FFA123FAC46B66" box="[1156,1307,1320,1343]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Prunus avium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), Persimmon (
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E9088A141FD4B6B38" box="[499,660,1353,1377]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="kaki">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E9088A141FD4B6B38" box="[499,660,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Diospyros kaki</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), common Walnut (
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E9214A142FBDF6B38" box="[879,1024,1353,1377]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Juglandaceae" genus="Juglans" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="regia">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E9214A142FBDF6B38" box="[879,1024,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Juglans regia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and grapes (
<bibRefCitation id="BD46AE8CD726525E95D9A142FAB86B38" author="Ferreira M. A. S. &amp; Ramos N. &amp; Soares C. &amp; Fernandes J. E." box="[1186,1383,1353,1377]" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" pagination="56 - 57" refId="ref9802" refString="Ferreira M. A. S., Ramos N., Soares C., Fernandes J. E. 2007. O acaro do-abacateiro no Algarve. Frutas, Legumes e Flores, 97: 56 - 57." type="journal article" year="2007">
Ferreira 
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E9588A141FAF26B38" box="[1267,1325,1353,1377]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
), being included in the INIAV collection. In 2020, 
<taxonomicName id="1ED7A8FED726525E92C7A167FBEC6BDD" authorityName="Tuttle, Baker &amp; Abbatiello" authorityYear="1976" box="[956,1075,1388,1412]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetranychidae" genus="Oligonychus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="8" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="perseae">
<emphasis id="EBA30F6FD726525E92C7A167FBEC6BDD" box="[956,1075,1388,1412]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">O. perseae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was found causing significant damage to avocado in the Óbidos region, centre 
<collectingCountry id="A1C093EDD726525E92CFA185FBCB6BFF" box="[948,1044,1422,1446]" name="Portugal" pageId="8" pageNumber="387">Portugal</collectingCountry>
, suggesting a significant northern extension of its known distribution range.
</paragraph>
